OL,3,CMore protection for blind people from
OL,4,Cpolice impersonators
OL,6,FThe VIP was first developed by the
OL,7,FRoyal National Institute of Blind
OL,8,FPeople in 2020, and has already been
OL,9,Fadopted by Lancashire and Merseyside
OL,10,FPolice.
OL,12,FTerri Balon, RNIB Regional Campaigner
OL,13,Ffor the North West, said: "Many blind
OL,14,Fand partially sighted people express
OL,15,Fconcern about being able to identify
OL,16,Fpeople they don't know, particularly
OL,17,Fthose that might knock on their door
OL,18,Fclaiming to be a police officer, or
OL,19,Findeed another official."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
