OL,3,CMore protection for blind people from
OL,4,Cpolice impersonators
OL,6,FThe protocol can be used by any blind
OL,7,For visually impaired person when a
OL,8,Fsupposed officer knocks on their door.
OL,10,FIf an officer has turned up
OL,11,Funannounced, such as during door-to-
OL,12,Fdoor enquiries, the non-emergency line
OL,13,Fcan be called and an operator will
OL,14,Fconfirm they are who they say they are.
OL,16,FFor pre-arranged police visits,
OL,17,Foperators can also set up passwords
OL,18,Fthe officer must provide before
OL,19,Fthey're allowed to enter the home.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
