OL,3,CMore protection for blind people from
OL,4,Cpolice impersonators
OL,6,FSergeant Kerry Smith explained how the
OL,7,Fprotocol works: "When somebody calls
OL,8,Fthe police, they can let us know they
OL,9,Fhave a visual impairment and our call
OL,10,Fhandlers will set up a password
OL,11,Fsecurity system with them.
OL,13,F"When the officer arrives, they knock
OL,14,Fon the door and say 'we're from the
OL,15,Fpolice, we've got your password' and
OL,16,Fthat means the person on the other
OL,17,Fside knows it's a genuine officer and
OL,18,Fthey can let them in."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
